        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Using the latest RC1 Zend and Skeleton Application.\r\n\r\nCreate two or more modules and add an en_US.mo file to each of the language folders.\r\n\r\nIn your config\/application.config.php file add the modules: 'modules' => array('Application', 'Test')\r\nNow when you visit the site only the translations in \"Test\" are actually translated. All translations in Application are not. Comment out \"Test\" in the modules configuration and now Application is translating just fine.\r\n\r\nAt this moment only the last module listed in the configuration is actually being translated."
        },
