        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/51415",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dasprid",
                        "name": "dasprid",
                        "displayName": "Ben Scholzen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Each module must use its own text domain.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dasprid",
                        "name": "dasprid",
                        "displayName": "Ben Scholzen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-07-26T15:03:39.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-07-26T15:03:39.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/51416",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=diemuzi",
                        "name": "diemuzi",
                        "displayName": "Sammie S. Taunton",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Ben,\r\n\r\nAm I missing something then? Because the latest skeleton has this support already. All I did was as stated above and then use $this->translate('SomeID'); in the view.\r\n\r\nEach Module configuration has:\r\n\r\n    'service_manager' => array(\r\n        'factories' => array(\r\n            'translator' => 'Zend\\I18n\\Translator\\TranslatorServiceFactory',\r\n        ),\r\n    ),\r\n    'translator' => array(\r\n        'locale' => 'en_US',\r\n        'translation_patterns' => array(\r\n            array(\r\n                'type'     => 'gettext',\r\n                'base_dir' => __DIR__ . '\/..\/language',\r\n                'pattern'  => '%s.mo',\r\n            ),\r\n        ),\r\n    ),\r\n\r\nSo all I should need to do is create a language directory inside of that module and then call $this->translate('SomeID'); and it should be translated from the en_US.mo file contained within that modules language directory.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=diemuzi",
                        "name": "diemuzi",
                        "displayName": "Sammie S. Taunton",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-07-26T15:05:16.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-07-26T15:11:47.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/51417",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=diemuzi",
                        "name": "diemuzi",
                        "displayName": "Sammie S. Taunton",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Can you please give clarification to this issue. Based on the Skeleton App there is no textdomain settings in the config\/module.config.php file for setting this missing option.\r\n\r\nI don't want to be a pain but saying each module must use it's own textdomain isn't much of an answer when something like this isn't clear. The documentation at this moment also shows nothing of a setup like the default SkeletonApp currently has in it's configs.\r\n\r\nI really appreciate it.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=diemuzi",
                        "name": "diemuzi",
                        "displayName": "Sammie S. Taunton",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-07-26T15:26:48.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-07-26T15:26:48.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/51422",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Marking this as a documentation improvement.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-07-26T16:00:50.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-07-26T16:00:50.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/51532",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=diemuzi",
                        "name": "diemuzi",
                        "displayName": "Sammie S. Taunton",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "After much headache and having to look at the source I think I've resolved this issue.\r\n\r\nIn the translator_patterns a new option needs to be provided as 'text_domain' => 'someidgoeshere'\r\n\r\nThen when you do echo $this->translate('translationtexthere', 'someidgoeshere');\r\n\r\nI'd update the documentation myself but the current documentation does not state anything about how to use the default SkeletonApp setup. The documentation only provides information from a factory setup.\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=diemuzi",
                        "name": "diemuzi",
                        "displayName": "Sammie S. Taunton",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-08-03T23:07:34.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-08-03T23:07:34.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
    },
